entries.title: Iran executes two more protesters over the weekend
entries.description: In Iran, two young men, one karate champion and a volunteer children's coach, were executed in connection with nationwide protests. CNN correspondent Jomana Karadsheh reports.

entries.title: A green comet will appear in the night sky for the first time in 50,000 years
entries.description: A recently discovered comet will soon make an appearance in the night sky for the first time in 50,000 years.

entries.title: The key takeaways from Prince Harry's explosive memoir
entries.description: Britain's Prince Harry has launched a series of incendiary accusations against members of his family in his new memoir, which reveals a number of private confrontations between him and other senior royals and details his split from the family.

entries.title: Former Twitter employees get severance offer after months of waiting. Many are unhappy with it
entries.description: After months of uncertainty and feeling left in the dark, many former Twitter employees impacted by a mass layoff in early November began receiving their severance offers over the weekend. But some are frustrated by the offer and the conditions attached to it.

entries.title: Classified documents from Biden's time as VP discovered in private office
entries.description: Several classified documents from President Joe Biden's time as vice president were discovered last fall in a private office, a source with knowledge of the matter tells CNN.

entries.title: House reconvenes to vote on rules package as some in GOP voice concern over concessions to hardliners
McCarthy faces key test as House reconvenes to vote on rules package
Why is Wall Street cheery all of a sudden?
entries.description: It's only early January, but so far in 2023 the pendulum on Wall Street has swung (to paraphrase Billy Joel) from sadness to euphoria.

entries.title: Bolsonaro, in the US since Dec. 30, has been hospitalized, wife says
entries.description: Former Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro was admitted to a hospital on Monday, according to his wife Michelle Bolsonaro.

entries.title: CNN correspondent breaks down Prince Harry's latest accusation
entries.description: CNN correspondent Max Foster weighs in on Prince Harry accusing Camilla, Queen Consort, of leaking stories about the family to the British media.

entries.title: Russian troops make fresh attempt to advance on town near Bakhmut after retreat
Ozone layer on track to recover within decades as harmful chemicals phased out
entries.description: In rare good news for the planet, Earth's ozone layer is on track to recover completely within decades, as ozone-depleting chemicals are phased out across the world, according to a new United Nations-backed assessment.

entries.title: Bloody knife found in basement of missing Massachusetts mother's home
entries.description: Investigators looking into the disappearance of a Massachusetts woman found a bloody knife in the basement of the home she shares with her husband and accused him of misleading police, a prosecutor with the Norfolk District Attorney's office said in court Monday.

entries.title: Federal regulators investigating Musk Tesla 'Full Self Driving' tweet
entries.description: Federal regulators want to know what Elon Musk meant in a Tweet about disabling driver alerts on Tesla's "Full Self Driving" driver assist system.

entries.title: Georgia grand jury investigating Trump and 2020 election aftermath completes its work
Fmr. US attorney on what could happen next in Georgia probe
entries.description: CNN's Sara Murray and former US attorney Michael Moore discuss the new court filing showing the Atlanta-area special grand jury investigating whether former President Donald Trump and his allies violated the law in their efforts to overturn the 2020 election has completed its work.

entries.title: How to eat to live longer, according to a new study
entries.description: You can reduce your risk of an early death for any reason by nearly 20%, just by eating more foods from your choice of four healthy eating patterns, according to a new study.

entries.title: Virgin Orbit counts down to first space launch ever from UK soil
entries.description: Virgin Orbit is about to conduct the first ever space launch from UK soil.

entries.title: Deere gives US farmers long-sought ability to repair their own tractors
entries.description: US farmers will have the right to repair tractors and other agricultural equipment from John Deere without having to use the manufacturer's own parts and facilities, under an agreement the company signed Sunday with farm industry representatives.

entries.title: Anderson Cooper reflects on his interview with Prince Harry
entries.description: Anderson Cooper joins "CNN This Morning" to talk about his latest interview with Prince Harry on "60 Minutes," in which he details dealing with the loss of his mother, Princess Diana.

entries.title: Five-time winner of world's best restaurant to close next year
entries.description: Noma, one of the most feted restaurants in the world, is set to close its doors to diners next year.

entries.title: Georgia grand jury investigating Trump and 2020 election aftermath completes its work
entries.description: The Atlanta-area special grand jury investigating whether former President Donald Trump and his allies violated the law in their efforts to overturn the 2020 election has completed its work, according to a new court filing.

entries.title: Football superstar Gareth Bale retires after trophy-laden career
entries.description: Five-time Champions League winner and Welsh football icon Gareth Bale has retired at the age of 33.

entries.title: Lizzo says cancel culture has become 'misused and misdirected'
entries.description: Lizzo wants to discuss cancel culture.

entries.title: A 6-year-old shot a teacher in class. Hear from an 8-year-old student who was down the hall
entries.description: A 6-year-old boy is in police custody after shooting a teacher at Richneck Elementary School in Newport News, Virginia. CNN's Poppy Harlow speaks to a father and his 8-year-old son who attends the school, addressing their concerns around safety.

entries.title: Iraqis celebrate their comeback with soccer tournament after decades of isolation
entries.description: Iraq is holding its first international soccer tournament in more than four decades, hosting its Gulf Arab neighbors for a two-week competition as it emerges from its worst and longest political deadlock in years.

entries.title: Dead NASA satellite returns to Earth after 38 years
entries.description: A defunct NASA satellite has fallen back to Earth after 38 years orbiting the planet.

entries.title: CNN anchor warns Brazil riot is 'real world impact' of Jan. 6
entries.description: Hundreds of supporters of former Brazilian president Jair Bolsonaro stormed major government buildings in the country's capital city Brasilia. The breaches come about a week after the inauguration of Lula da Silva, who returned to power after he defeated Bolsonaro in a run-off election. CNN's John Avlon discusses how the incident is reminiscent of January 6, 2021, when rioters stormed the US Capitol in an effort to prevent the certification of the 2020 election.

entries.title: Why high-tech stadiums are 'the new cathedrals'
entries.description: CNN finds out how technology is shaping the future of stadium design and helping sports fans to connect with each other.

entries.title: Opinion: In Brazil, a stunning attack on democracy
entries.description: For my family, it was supposed to be a lazy Sunday -- we were enjoying "caipirinhas" and other traditional Brazilian fare during our final day in the country after three weeks of holiday vacation.

entries.title: Hear why Biden's border visit is receiving bipartisan criticism
entries.description: President Joe Biden visited the US-Mexico border on Sunday for the first time as president, but he did not appear to see or meet with migrants. CNN correspondent Rosa Flores reports.

entries.title: From color-changing cars to self-driving strollers, here's some of the coolest tech from CES 2023
entries.description: A long list of companies once again showed off an assortment of cutting edge technology and oddball gadgets at the Consumer Electronics Show in Las Vegas last week.

entries.title: Ukrainians spend Orthodox Christmas in a shelter after cease fire 'never materialized'
entries.description: CNN's Ben Wedeman joins Ukrainians in a bomb shelter as they try to celebrate Orthodox Christmas hiding away from Russian shelling.

entries.title: South Africa's Eskom says police investigating alleged poisoning of CEO
entries.description: South African power utility Eskom on Sunday said police were investigating whether an attempt was made to poison its outgoing chief executive officer, Andre de Ruyter.

entries.title: Workers in China clash with police after reported layoffs at Covid test maker
entries.description: Workers at a Chinese factory making Covid-19 test kits clashed with police over the weekend after their managers apparently told them to go on vacation early, a move that effectively terminated their employment without notice, according to social media posts and videos reviewed by CNN.

entries.title: Bonds are back, but for how long?
entries.description: Stocks soared on Friday to their best day in more than a month. The Dow gained 700 points and the S&P 500 and Nasdaq rose by 2.3% and 2.6% respectively, as traders bet that a slowdown in wage growth could mean that inflation may finally be cooling off.

entries.title: The violent attack on Brazil's government was months in the making. Here's what you need to know
The violent attack on Brazil's government was months in the making. Here's what you need to know
entries.description: Brazil was reeling Monday after hundreds of supporters of the country's former leader Jair Bolsonaro stormed the seats of power in the capital Brasilia, trashing offices and drawing condemnation from the government and the international community.

entries.title: Opening statements set for today in trial of man accused of killing 8 in NYC bike path attack, the first death penalty case under Biden
entries.description: Opening statements are set to begin Monday in the trial of Sayfullo Saipov, who faces federal terrorism charges for allegedly running down pedestrians with a rented truck on Manhattan's West Side bike path on Halloween 2017, killing eight people.

entries.title: Jon Rahm produces stunning comeback to win Tournament of Champions in Hawaii
entries.description: Spanish golfer Jon Rahm won his third PGA Tour title in six starts with a stunning comeback to overturn a seven-shot deficit at the Tournament of Champions in Hawaii.

entries.title: Pentagon prepares for series of GOP-led investigations
entries.description: Pentagon officials have held multiple high-level meetings in recent months in preparation for a barrage of Republican-led House investigations into issues varying from the US withdrawal from Afghanistan withdrawal to what conservative lawmakers have deemed "woke" military policies, according to a senior defense official.

entries.title: How to watch Georgia Bulldogs vs. TCU Horned Frogs in the College Football Playoff National Championship
entries.description: And so, it all comes down to this. On Monday evening, either the Georgia Bulldogs or the Texas Christian University (TCU) Horned Frogs will be crowned college football's best team.

entries.title: Goldman Sachs will lay off up to 3,200 workers this week

entries.title: UK officials meet with unions in bid to end strikes by nurses and ambulance drivers
entries.description: Senior UK government officials are meeting with labor unions on Monday in a last-ditch effort to avert another wave of strikes affecting vital public services such as health care and transport.

entries.title: Claire Danes and Hugh Dancy are expecting their third child
entries.description: "Homeland" star Claire Danes and fellow actor Hugh Dancy will be welcoming another baby into the family this year.

entries.title: Rising MMA star Victoria Lee dies at 18
entries.description: Victoria Lee, one of the brightest new stars in mixed martial arts (MMA), has died at the age of 18, her sister confirmed.

entries.title: JJ Watt receives emotional standing ovation after final NFL game following end of stellar career
entries.description: JJ Watt struggled to hold back his tears as he received a standing ovation while he left the NFL field for the final time after his likely Hall of Fame career came to an end on Sunday.

entries.title: Josh Allen describes kickoff return touchdown in first play since Damar Hamlin's cardiac arrest as 'spiritual'
entries.description: Josh Allen could barely hold back his emotions as he described Nyheim Hines' kick return touchdown in the Buffalo Bills' first play since teammate Damar Hamlin suffered a cardiac arrest.

entries.title: Museum of Sex to open new outpost in Miami
entries.description: Combining the profound and the playful, the Museum of Sex has become one of New York City's top-rated attractions on TripAdvisor since it opened in Manhattan in 2002.

entries.title: Biden struggles to confirm judges in the South and thwart Trump's impact

entries.title: Houston Texans fire head coach Lovie Smith after one season

entries.title: This giant economy wants its workers to get inflation-busting pay rises

entries.title: Why reclining seats are vanishing from airplanes

entries.title: NFL playoffs set following Green Bay Packers loss to the Detroit Lions
entries.description: The NFL playoffs are set following the Green Bay Packers 20-16 loss to the Detroit Lions Sunday night.

entries.title: When too much daydreaming becomes a disorder
entries.description: Despite what we're often taught to believe, daydreaming can be immensely useful. Not only can it be a source of pleasure and a way to relieve boredom, research shows that our ability to mentally escape the present can also boost creativity, problem-solving and planning, and provide an antidote to loneliness.

entries.title: In pictures: Bolsonaro supporters storm Brazilian Congress

entries.title: This Nigerian artist wants you to be inspired by Black women

'Everything starts to become better': After three years of Covid isolation, China opens its gates

entries.description: Storm-battered California communities are bracing for another round of likely flooding, mudslides, toppled trees and power outages as the latest in an unrelenting parade of atmospheric rivers hits the West Coast Monday, with Gov. Gavin Newsom warning officials "expect to to see the worst of it still in front of us."

entries.description: Negotiations aimed at averting a nurses strike at two major New York City hospitals went past a midnight deadline with a walk-out by 7,000 nurses looming as soon as 6 am ET Monday.

Pakistan to seek $16 billion to rebuild flood-hit country at UN conference

entries.description: The longest battle for House speaker in 164 years finally ended early Saturday, culminating with the GOP's Kevin McCarthy being elected on the 15th ballot. It should've been the most stirring moment after days of Republican struggle on the House floor, but it wasn't.
